---
layout: 'default'
title: 'Home'
---

.hero-unit
  h1
    span.know know
    | 
    span.cujo cujo
    span.js JS
  p Your source for everything you may want to learn about cujoJS, including getting started tutorials and sample applications.

.row
  .span8
    - var post = getFiles({ layout: 'post' }, { ctime: -1 }).toJSON()[0]
    if post && post.contentRenderedWithoutLayouts
      h2 Recently Blogged
      h3(style='margin-top: 0')= post.title
      div!= post.contentRenderedWithoutLayouts.split('<a name="jump"></a>')[0]
      p: a(href=post.url + '#jump') Continue reading...
      p: a.btn(href='/blog') All blog posts

    h2 Latest tutorials
    nav.linklist
      ul
        each tutorial in getFiles({ layout: 'tutorial' }, { ctime: -1 }).toJSON().slice(0, 8)
          li
            p
              span= formatDate(tutorial.ctime)
              |  &raquo;&nbsp;
              a(href=tutorial.url)= tutorial.title
              if tutorial.summary
                span= ' - ' + tutorial.summary

    p: a.btn(href="/tutorials") All tutorials

  .span4
    h2 Get cujoJS
    p Download the latest versions of each library.
    p: a.btn(href="/downloads") Get cujoJS

    h2 Reference docs
    p Complete reference documentation for each cujoJS library.
    p: a.btn(href="/documentation") Reference docs

    h2 Sample apps
    p Sample applications apply cujoJS concepts within a specific domain.
    p: a.btn(href="/samples") Samples apps

    h2 Need assistance?
    :markdown
      Join cujoJS's [mailing list](https://groups.google.com/d/forum/cujojs) where you can find solutions, get the latest news, or share successes.
      If you prefer live discussion, join the [#cujojs room on freenode](irc://irc.freenode.net:6697/#cujojs).

      Professional support packages are available from [SitePen](http://www.sitepen.com/support/).
